      "writtenOn": "2017-09-19T17:57:49Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I was a bit conflicted about this.\n\nI allow connection_ to be nullptr for now, just for some self unit tests where making a real ptrace connection can\u0027t happen. We could pass in an uninitialized DirectPtraceConnection, but that seems wrong. I was also thinking of making a FakePtraceConnection for testing or a SelfPtraceConnection with a partial implementation.\n\nCurrently, ProcessReader can do everything except call Threads() with a nullptr connection_.",
      "parentUuid": "ffb92254_40daaa1c",
      "revId": "31e44b190616d0a92ec1d8b173e2d67380a5bcbe",
